---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('mass');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">Density, not volume.</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Mass</strong> is the substance and depth that builds around the Identity Stem.
					It is not how much surface you occupy. It is how much stake you actually own:
					commitment with weight, history, and resistance to casual displacement.
				</p>
				<p>
					In the framework, Mass also carries a relativistic analogy:
					mass as rest potential that can convert into real agency energy under <strong class="text-white/80">coherent velocity along the stem</strong> (<code class="text-violet-300">E ≈ m c²</code> as inspirational formalization, not a physics claim).
					High mass without direction is inertia. Mass with coherent motion becomes force.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Engineering</div>
				<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">What you work on</h2>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Owned stake:</strong> depth you can defend without performance.
						What would still pull if applause vanished?
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Density over spread:</strong> fewer domains with real weight beat
						many thin affiliations.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Conversion:</strong> convert rest mass into agency by moving
						coherently along the stem (State Differential and Vision Gradient aligned).
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<p>
					Mass alone does not define identity. It gives the stem inertia and pull.
					Curvature warps possibility space around that weight. Gravitation is what others feel as attraction.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="mass" />
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
</style>
